'''Abjection''', ''[[noun (part of speech)|noun]]'' [F. ''abjection'', L. ''abjectio''.]

<ol>
<li>The act of bringing down or [[humbling]].

<code>The ''abjection'' of the king and his realm.</code> ''[[Joe (source)|Joe]].''

<li> The state of being rejected or cast out. [R.]

<code>An ''adjection'' from the beatific regions where God, and his angels and saints, dwell forever. ''[[Jer. Taylor (source)|Jer. Taylor]].''</code>

<li> A low or [[downcast]] state; [[meanness]] of spirit; [[abasement]]; [[degradation]].

<code>That this should be termed baseness, ''abjection'' of mind, or servility, is it credible? ''[[Hooker (source)|Hooker]].''</code>
</ol>